The paper deals with a matching problem with preferences and capacity constraints, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and economics. The use of order weighted averages (OWAs) draws inspiration from multi-criteria decision making and voting, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of task and resource allocation is also relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the observation of a connection between the model and the proportional multi-winner election problem in social choice suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
